            "body": "<p><strong>Please Note:<\/strong> This is <strong>not advised<\/strong> to keep any business or data access logic in JSPs. JSPs are meant for presentation purpose ONLY. Such data access related code should be moved in server side JAVA classes. Please read about <strong>MVC<\/strong>(Model-View-Controller) pattern to learn more.<\/p>\n\n<p>Get a <code>statement<\/code> object using your <code>connection<\/code>, pass your string query and run <code>executeUpdate<\/code> as below:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>   conn1.open();\n   Statement statement = conn1.createStatement();\n   statement.executeUpdate(insert);\n   conn1.close();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 13042551,
            "question_id": 13042522,
            "last_edit_date": 1351049524
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/J5ujJ.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 18600,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 42769,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/42769/adeel-ansari",
